---
import FaqAccordion from '@/components/FaqAccordion.astro'
---

<section class="section section--tint s8-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <h2 class="s8-faq__heading">Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <FaqAccordion items={[
      {
        question: "What exactly is NAD+?",
        answer_html: "<p>NAD+ (Nicotinamide Adenine Dinucleotide) is a coenzyme found in every cell of your body that is essential for energy production, DNA repair, and regulating hundreds of metabolic processes. It is a critical molecule for life, and its levels naturally decline as we age.</p>",
      },
      {
        question: "How does NAD+ relate to aging?",
        answer_html: "<p>As we age, NAD+ levels in our cells can drop by as much as 50%. This decline is directly linked to many hallmarks of aging, including decreased energy, slower metabolism, reduced cognitive function, and an impaired ability to repair cellular damage. By replenishing NAD+ levels, we can support the body's natural repair mechanisms.</p>",
      },
      {
        question: "Who is an ideal candidate for NAD+ IV Therapy?",
        answer_html: "<p>NAD+ IV therapy is beneficial for a wide range of individuals, including those experiencing chronic fatigue or brain fog, athletes seeking enhanced recovery, individuals interested in anti-aging and longevity, and those looking to support their overall cellular health. A brief consultation with our team will help determine if it is the right fit for you.</p>",
      },
      {
        question: "Are there any side effects during the NAD+ infusion?",
        answer_html: "<p>Some clients experience mild and temporary sensations during the infusion, such as slight nausea, a feeling of tightness in the chest, or lightheadedness. These are normal responses and are managed by slowing the infusion rate. Our staff is trained to ensure your comfort throughout the entire session.</p>",
      },
      {
        question: "How many NAD+ sessions will I need?",
        answer_html: "<p>The number of sessions depends on your individual health goals. For general wellness and a noticeable energy boost, many clients benefit from a series of 3-5 initial sessions. For more significant anti-aging or therapeutic goals, a longer protocol may be recommended. Our team will work with you to create a personalized plan.</p>",
      },
    ]} />
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .s8-faq__heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
    font-weight: var(--weight-regular);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
</style>
